`frontend-microinteraction-pass` is blocked, not complete. On April 16, 2026, all local write paths failed: `exec_command` returned `Failed to create unified exec process: No such file or directory`, `js_repl` returned `failed to start Node runtime: No such file or directory`, and `apply_patch` also failed with `No such file or directory`. Because of that, I could not persist the findings into `audit-map/` files, so I am not claiming pass completion.

What I did verify, using the GitHub connector against `Raed2180416/AirMentor` `main`, is still useful. `src/telemetry.ts`, `src/startup-diagnostics.ts`, [src/App.tsx](/home/raed/projects/air-mentor-ui/src/App.tsx), and [src/system-admin-app.tsx](/home/raed/projects/air-mentor-ui/src/system-admin-app.tsx) show that startup diagnostics are emitted as silent structured telemetry on both academic and sysadmin surfaces, with a user-visible hard stop only for sysadmin when `VITE_AIRMENTOR_API_BASE_URL` is missing. `src/proof-provenance.ts` is the canonical copy contract for provenance and count-source wording, and that wording is reused across the academic summary strip, faculty profile, HoD analytics, risk explorer, student shell, and system-admin proof dashboard. `src/proof-playback.ts`, [src/academic-workspace-content-shell.tsx](/home/raed/projects/air-mentor-ui/src/academic-workspace-content-shell.tsx), [src/academic-workspace-route-surface.tsx](/home/raed/projects/air-mentor-ui/src/academic-workspace-route-surface.tsx), and the proof bootstrap logic in [src/App.tsx](/home/raed/projects/air-mentor-ui/src/App.tsx) confirm the restore/reset/invalidation lifecycle: saved checkpoint selection is read from localStorage, invalid or inaccessible checkpoints are cleared, academic routes share the restore banner, and the sysadmin dashboard adds its own sessionStorage-backed checkpoint-tab behavior.

Two important blockers remain. First, exhaustive `src/` tail mapping is still incomplete because I could not recover local shell access. Second, GitHub `main` still exposes the legacy `audit/` corpus rather than the local `audit-map/` operating system, so the remote fallback was good enough to validate source and test files but not the local audit baseline.

Manual action required: repair the native Codex local shell and patch toolchain so local reads and writes work again. Exact resume point: continue `frontend-microinteraction-pass` from the three mapped families above, then persist into `audit-map/12-frontend-microinteractions/`, `audit-map/23-coverage/`, `audit-map/24-agent-memory/`, and the affected `15-final-maps/` files. Exact next prompt: `AirMentor audit OS pass: frontend-microinteraction-pass resume from 2026-04-16 shell blocker; finish remaining src tail inventory and reconcile local-vs-remote drift`.
